==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Actinomycosis
<hw>Ac`ti*no*my*co"sis</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧k`t⟦icr⟧*n⟦osl⟧*m⟦imac⟧*k⟦omac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A chronic infectious disease of
cattle and man due to infection with actinomycetes, especially by
<spn>Actinomyces bovis</spn> in cattle and by <spn>Actinomyces
israeli</spn> or <spn>Arachnia propionica</spn> in man. It is
characterized by hard swellings usually in the mouth and jaw. In man the
disease may also affect the abdomen or thorax. In cattle it is called
also <altname>lumpy jaw</altname> or <altname>big
jaw</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Actinomycotic</ent>⟦br⟧
